- cs.DM (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new iterative algorithm for clustering data points in a semi-metric space, which involves designing and analyzing algorithms for processing and organizing data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper presents a clustering algorithm, which is a common technique in machine learning for grouping similar data points together. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper applies the proposed algorithm to a real network dataset, which falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new algorithm for clustering data points, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence that deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the computational and memory complexity of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
